docs\progress\logs\20260625-031229_gen-requirement-5.log:3297:I need to stop covering manual tasks and focus on loops and parallel processes. I’m wondering if I should handle duplicate events. The issue seems to stem from the manual runTask, which sets the status to running before the executeTask does. It appears that the starting event likely resides in executeTask, which could cover manual, concurrent, and looping processes in one spot. It’s interesting to consider how all this connects!
docs\progress\logs\20260625-031229_gen-requirement-5.log:3299:计划内容已经成型；我再确认时间工具位置，方便把 UI scope 标准确。
